This project is a prototype for a video playback component in a software as a service product.

The component will be used to playback video content from a remote source.

The component will be used in a web application that will be used to playback video content.

Our primary goal is to support realtime playback of arbitrary supplied video URLs.

For now, we'll start by supporting a small subset of video formats.

Formats we'll support must be seekable. That is, we need to be able to efficiently seek to random access points in the video, and transcode to a lower bitrate segment using a just-in-time approach.

Assume we will not need to defensively code around multiple ffpmeg versions, we control the deployment environment, and we currently have ffmpeg 6.1.

[package.json](mdc:package.json) contains build scripts

We're NOT building a re-usable piece of software. This is for a production system, we do not need to create lots of options and branches for every contingency. We control the inputs to this and make simplifying assumptions.

Only make changes to solve the current request. Do not make unrelated improvements to code quality or for other purposes. Those changes should be made only upon request.

Use `npx tsx` to execute typescript files.
